#compdef wasmoon
# =============================================================================
# wasmoon ‚Äî Adrian Ceifa's "A real lua 5.4 VM with JS
#           bindings made with webassembly" ‚Äî a Node.js
#           / browser package that ships a complete
#           Lua 5.4 interpreter compiled to
#           WebAssembly + a TypeScript-friendly JS API
#           for embedding Lua scripting in Node.js,
#           Deno, Bun, Cloudflare Workers, and any
#           browser-context JavaScript runtime.
#           Unlike fengari (pure JS Lua 5.3 port) which
#           is slower but JS-native, wasmoon takes the
#           upstream Lua C source + Emscripten-compiles
#           it to WASM, giving near-C performance while
#           remaining serializable across JS contexts.
#           Distinguishing from fengari (pure-JS Lua 5.3,
#           slower), node-lua (deprecated cgo bindings),
#           lua-in-js (older + slower), lualib-js (older),
#           and various server-only Lua runtimes
#           (gopher-lua needs Go, mlua needs Rust) by:
#             - LUA 5.4 SUPPORT ‚Äî supports the latest
#               stable Lua spec including integer/float
#               separation, goto labels, bitwise
#               operators (`|`, `&`, `~`, `<<`, `>>`,
#               `~`), to-be-closed variables (`<close>`),
#               const variables (`<const>`).  fengari +
#               most other JS Lua libs are stuck at
#               Lua 5.1 or 5.3
#             - WASM COMPILATION ‚Äî Emscripten-compiles
#               upstream lua-5.4 source to WebAssembly;
#               near-C performance for pure-Lua code;
#               JS boundary crossings are the main
#               overhead
#             - TYPESCRIPT-FIRST API ‚Äî `LuaFactory`,
#               `LuaEngine`, `LuaThread`, `LuaTable`
#               TypeScript classes with full type
#               definitions; idiomatic for TS callers
#             - DECORATE / PROXY ‚Äî `decorate(jsObject,
#                { disableProxy: false })` exposes
#               JavaScript objects to Lua with optional
#               Proxy-based property interception;
#               Lua scripts can call `.foo` on JS
#               objects + get JS values back
#             - DOCEMPTY / DOFILE / DOSTRING ‚Äî
#               familiar Lua C API entry points exposed
#               as TypeScript async methods
#             - MOUNT VIRTUAL FILESYSTEM ‚Äî `factory.
#               mountFile(path, content)` adds files
#               to the Emscripten WASM virtual
#               filesystem; Lua's `require` + `dofile`
#               can load them
#             - GOROUTINE-LIKE COROUTINES ‚Äî Lua 5.4
#               coroutines + JS Promises bridge
#               cleanly; can `coroutine.yield()` to JS
#               Promise resolution
#             - BROWSER-COMPATIBLE ‚Äî runs in any
#               browser; the WASM bundle is ~250KB
#               gzipped; suitable for in-browser Lua
#               playgrounds, configuration editors,
#               game modding tools
#             - CLI MODE ‚Äî `wasmoon script.lua` runs
#               a Lua script from the command line;
#               `-l file` mounts files into the
#               virtual filesystem; `-i` forces
#               interactive REPL after script
#               execution
#             - REPL ‚Äî interactive REPL with readline
#               history; press Ctrl-D to exit
#             - 671+ STARS ‚Äî popular among
#               JavaScript-side Lua embedding users;
#               growing as Lua 5.4 adoption increases
#               (Roblox's Luau is technically Lua 5.1+
#               extensions, not standard Lua 5.4)
#           Used by: JavaScript / TypeScript developers
#           wanting to embed Lua scripting in their
#           applications (game configuration editors,
#           web-based Lua sandboxes, browser-side
#           Roblox-style scripting environments,
#           Cloudflare Workers running user-supplied
#           Lua plugins), educators teaching Lua via
#           browser-based playgrounds, and Roblox
#           tooling developers (though Roblox's actual
#           Lua dialect Luau differs from standard
#           Lua 5.4).
#
# Author:  Adrian Ceifa (ceifa on GitHub).  License: MIT.
#          Active development.
# Source:  https://github.com/ceifa/wasmoon
#          https://github.com/ceifa/wasmoon/blob/main/bin/wasmoon
