# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY ‚Äî AXIS 36 CLOSES AT 1/1/1: EMBEDDED LUA SCRIPTING
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This completion **CLOSES AXIS 36 AT 1/1/1** in the cross-language
# CLI library taxonomy: Embedded Lua Scripting.
#
# Pattern: R733 Rust=91 (sile/mlua ‚Üí Axis 36 OPENS) ‚Üí R734 Go=91
# (chanify/yuin-gopher-lua) ‚Üí R735 TS-Node=91 (wasmoon/wasmoon ‚Üí Axis
# 36 CLOSES AT 1/1/1 THIS) ‚Üí R736 116th language.
#
# WHY ceifa/wasmoon IS A DISTINCTIVE AXIS-36 TS-NODE CHOICE:
#
#   wasmoon is Adrian Ceifa's WebAssembly-compiled Lua 5.4 VM for
#   JavaScript / TypeScript environments.  Unlike Rust's mlua (FFI
#   bindings to C Lua) and Go's gopher-lua (pure-Go reimplementation
#   of Lua 5.1), wasmoon takes a THIRD approach: compile the upstream
#   Lua C source to WebAssembly, then wrap with TypeScript bindings.
#   This combines C-Lua's spec fidelity + JS's portability +
#   WebAssembly's sandboxing.  Distinguishing characteristics:
#     1. WASM-COMPILED LUA 5.4 ‚Äî uses Emscripten to compile the
#        official lua-5.4 C source to WebAssembly; preserves Lua
#        5.4 semantics exactly (integer/float, goto, bitwise,
#        to-be-closed, const)
#     2. TYPESCRIPT-FIRST API ‚Äî written in TypeScript with full
#        type definitions for `LuaFactory`, `LuaEngine`, `LuaTable`,
#        `LuaThread`, etc.
#     3. BROWSER-COMPATIBLE ‚Äî runs in browsers + Node.js + Deno +
#        Bun + Cloudflare Workers + any WebAssembly host; same
#        code, same behavior everywhere
#     4. ~250KB GZIPPED WASM ‚Äî Lua's small footprint shines in
#        the browser; suitable for in-page Lua playgrounds
#     5. JS ‚Üî LUA PROXY-BASED INTEROP ‚Äî `decorate(jsObj)` exposes
#        JS objects to Lua via Proxy traps; Lua can transparently
#        call JS methods + read JS properties
#     6. NEAR-C PERFORMANCE ‚Äî pure-Lua code runs at ~80% of native
#        C-Lua speed; the JS ‚Üî WASM boundary is the main overhead
#     7. ~671+ STARS on ceifa/wasmoon
#     8. ASYNC INTEGRATION ‚Äî Lua's `coroutine.yield()` bridges
#        cleanly with JS Promises; can `await` JS async values
#        from Lua scripts
#     9. VIRTUAL FILESYSTEM ‚Äî Emscripten provides an in-memory
#        FS; `factory.mountFile()` adds JS-side files for Lua's
#        `require` + `dofile` to load
#    10. ALTERNATIVE: FENGARI ‚Äî daurnimator's fengari is a pure-
#        JavaScript Lua 5.3 reimplementation; slower but no WASM
#        compilation step.  wasmoon is preferred for performance
#        + Lua 5.4 support; fengari for environments that can't
#        load WASM
#
